Hey there! Just bought 2 ToF sensors from PlayingwithFusion, and we have the exact same problem as mentioned in previous posts on this subject: no way to access the configuration panel at <roboRio IP>:5812 like stated in the documentation.

RoboRio version: 2024 v2.1
Language: Java
PlayingWithFusion library version: 2024.01.28

Steps taken so far:

  • Made sure we instantiate the sensor with final TimeOfFlight sensor = new TimeOfFlight(0);
  • Deploy robot code
  • Access the roborio through cabled ethernet
  • Made sure we can access the Roborio panel at http://10.TE.AM.2
  • Tried to access the ToF configuration panel at http://10.TE.AM.2:5812

No luck. Then:

  • Access the roborio through USB
  • Made sure we can access the Roborio panel at http://172.22.11.2
  • Tried to access the ToF configuration panel at http://172.22.11.2:5812

No luck. Then:

  • Installed offline the PlayingWithFusion library version: 2024.00.21
  • Retried the above 2 tests.

Finally, we tried above 4 tests using both a radio configured at the competition for the field, and a radio configured for the pit. Same negative result.

No luck. Then, although the documentation does not mention simulation support, we still tried, out of completeness:

  • Launch simulation on the PC with the above 2 versions of the library.
  • Tried to access the ToF configuration panel at http://localhost:5812
  • Tried to access the ToF configuration panel at http://127.0.0.1:5812
  • Tried to access the ToF configuration panel at http://<local IP>:5812

We tried 2 different sensors. Each time the sensor is well connected, and the led is solid orange. We are conscious that whether a sensor is present or not should not matter when it comes to accessing the configuration panel, but we just wanted to be complete.

@JStein @JaredL any idea what could be wrong?

Thanks,

Julien

Could you try updating to version 2024.03.09 and let us know if you are still experiencing issues getting into the web interface.
